President Obama expresses his deepest condolences to the people of Japan, especially those who have lost loved ones in the recent earthquake and tsunamis. The United States is ready to provide assistance to Japan during this difficult time, as the friendship and alliance between the two nations remains strong. The President assures that the US will closely monitor tsunamis in Japan and the Pacific, and urges citizens in the affected region to listen to their state and local officials. FEMA has been instructed to be prepared to assist Hawaii and other potentially affected US states and territories.